Determine the output of the following code:

```java
for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
    for (int j = 1; j <= 2; j++) {
        System.out.print(i * j + " ");
    }
}
```

Determine the value of `count` after the following code executes:

```java
int count = 0;
for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
        count++;
    }
}
```

How many times does `System.out.println("*")` execute when the following code runs?

```java
for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < 5; j++) {
        System.out.println("*");
    }
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
    for (int j = 1; j <= i; j++) {
        System.out.print(j + " ");
    }
    System.out.println();
}
```

Determine the value of `sum` after the following code executes:

```java
int sum = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
    for (int j = 1; j <= i; j++) {
        sum += j;
    }
}
```

The following code is intended to print a 3×3 grid where each row displays `0 1 2 `. Which single change would make it produce the correct output?

```java
for (int r = 0; r < 3; r++) {
    for (int c = 0; c <= 3; c++) {
        System.out.print(c + " ");
    }
    System.out.println();
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
        if (i == j) {
            System.out.print(i + " ");
        }
    }
}
```

Consider the following nested loop where `n` equals `4`. How many times does `count++` execute?

```java
int count = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    for (int j = i; j <= n; j++) {
        count++;
    }
}
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= 4; i++) {
    for (int j = 1; j <= i; j++) {
        if (j % 2 == 0) {
x++;
        }
    }
}
System.out.println(x);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int i = 1;
while (i <= 3) {
    int j = 1;
    while (j <= 3) {
        System.out.print(i + j + " ");
        j++;
    }
    i++;
}
```

The following code is intended to print a right triangle where row `i` contains exactly `i` asterisks, for `i` from 1 to 3. Which single change would produce the intended output?

```java
int n = 3;
for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    for (int j = 1; j <= n; j++) {
        System.out.print("* ");
    }
    System.out.println();
}
```

